Quidgets
==============

A collection of helper widgets that directly bind to your database structure.
It's extremely simple to use.

HOW TO INSTALL

* Install plugin from git:
    ./script/plugin install git://github.com/phtphan/Quidgets.git

* In your /app/controllers/application_controller.rb, add this line : 
    enable_quidgets
    
    => Your applcation_controller.rb should look like this:
    
      class ApplicationController < ActionController::Base
        enable_quidgets
      end
    
    


HOW TO USE
  Example DB structure:
  + user.rb
      belongs_to :payment_method
    
  + payment_method.rb
      has_many :users
  


* CHECKBOX: checkbox(params) # :id, :class, :record, :field
  
    Ex: 
        <%= checkbox :id => "user_active", :record => @current_user, :field => :active %>
          
* RADIO BUTTON: radio(params) # :name, :id, :class, :parent, :option
    
    Ex:    
        PICK A PAYMENT METHOD <br/>
        <%= radio(:name => "payment_method_option", :parent => @user, :option => PaymentMethod.find(1)) VISA <br/>
        <%= radio(:name => "payment_method_option", :parent => @user, :option => PaymentMethod.find(2)) MASTER CARD <br/>            
      
* TEXTBOX: textbox(params)  # :id, :class, :record, :field

    <%= textbox(:id => "user_name", :record => user, :field => :name) %>
    
* LISTBOX: listbox(params) # :id, :class, :parent, :list
    <%= listbox(:id => "payment_method", :parent => @user, :list => PaymentMethod.all) %>        
    
* DROPBOX: dropbox(params) # :id, :class, :parent, :list
    <%= dropbox(:id => "payment_method", :parent => @user, :list => PaymentMethod.all)
    
* listbox_dragdrop(params) # Coming soon


